Heat dressing in large skillet on medium heat. Add chicken and garlic; cover. Cook 5 min. on each side or until chicken is browned. Remove from skillet; set aside. Add canned tomatoes and water to skillet. Stir in rice; bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 10 min. Return chicken to skillet. Sprinkle with cheese; cover. Cook on low heat 5 min. Top with tomato and cilantro.